         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>
               As a converted magician, a number of magical prayers are attributed to <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3247Cyprian">Cyprian of Antioch</t:persName>. 
               The Prayer of Cyprian is the main prayer, known in Greek, Latin, Syriac, Armenian and Georgian versions, 
               cp. <t:bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/599ZQT6Z"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Bausi1998Cipriano"/><title level="a">L’Epistola 70 di Cipriano di Cartagine in versione etiopica</title><title level="j">Aethiopica</title><author><forename>Alessandro</forename><surname>Bausi</surname></author><date>1998</date><biblScope unit="volume">1</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">101-130</biblScope><note type="url">http://journals.sub.uni-hamburg.de/aethiopica/article/view/650</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Literature</note><note type="tag">Philology</note><note type="tag">Textual criticism</note><note type="tag">bm:Bausi1998Cipriano</note></note><note type="tag">Ethiopic</note><note type="tag">Literature</note><note type="tag">Philology</note><note type="tag">Textual criticism</note><note type="tag">bm:Bausi1998Cipriano</note><t:citedRange unit="page">104</t:citedRange></t:bibl> and <t:bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/R2TCMID3"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Simon1936ReviewBilabel"/><title level="a">Review of Bilabel - Grothmann: Griechische, koptische und arabische Texte zur Religion und religiösen Literatur in Ägyptens Spätzeit</title><title level="j">Orientalia</title><author><forename>Jean</forename><surname>Simon</surname></author><date>1936</date><biblScope unit="volume">5</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">152-160</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Simon1936ReviewBilabel</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Simon1936ReviewBilabel</note></t:bibl>. 
               Both Arabic and Ethiopic traditions have a long and a short recension of this prayer, see <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3578Prayer">Ṣalot za-qǝddus
                                                  Qoṗrǝyānos</t:ref> and  <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3579Prayer">Ṣalot za-Qoṗrǝyānos
                                                  ba-za-yǝśǝʿʿǝr manāfǝst rǝkusān wa-ba-za-yāwaggǝz
                                                  sayṭānāt</t:ref>. 
            </t:p>
         </t:abstract>
